Create one server-only singleton context with `jazz-napi` installed directly, a stable persistent `dataPath`, `serverUrl`, and an unprefixed `BACKEND_SECRET`:
```ts
export const jazz = createJazzContext({
  appId: process.env.JAZZ_APP_ID!, app, permissions,
  driver: { type: "persistent", dataPath: "./jazz-data" },
  serverUrl: process.env.JAZZ_SERVER_URL,
  backendSecret: process.env.BACKEND_SECRET,
});
```
Reuse it for all requests; never create a context per request. Call `await jazz.shutdown()` during process shutdown (and `flush()` only when an explicit synchronous flush is needed). Keep `BACKEND_SECRET` and `JAZZ_ADMIN_SECRET` server-only; only app ID and server URL may be public. Use a memory driver only with an upstream durable `serverUrl`.
